<H2> Preconditions: </H2>

    <CODE>#include &quot;iodecl3.h&quot;</CODE> if called from C.
    <P> 

    Valid <CODE>YEAR, MONTH, MDAY</CODE> (and after the
    Gregorian-calendar transition, which happened 1582 and after&mdash;in
    1752 in the US).
    <P> 

        
<H2> Fortran Usage: </H2>
<PRE>
    ...
    INTEGER   JULIAN
    INTEGER   JDATE, YEAR
    ...
    YEAR  = 1988
    JDATE = 1000 * YEAR + JULIAN( YEAR, 3, 21 )
    !!....  Now JDATE is the Models-3 Julian date for March 21, 1988
    ...
</PRE><P> 

<H2> C Usage: </H2>
<PRE>
    ...
#include &quot;iodecl3.h&quot;                          
    ...
    int  jdate, year, month, mday ;
    ...
    year  = 1999 ;
    month =    4 ;
    mday  =    1 ,
    jdate = 1000 * year  +  julianc( year, month, mday ) ;
            /*  Now jdate is the Models-3 Julian date for 
                April Fool's Day, 1999                     */
    ...
</PRE><P> 


